The paper deals with personalized recommendation in location-based social networks (LBSNs), which involves modeling user behavior patterns and contextual scenarios. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.SOC (computational social science), and cs.DB (databases). Among these, cs.SI and cs.IR are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the problem of recommendation in social networks and the use of latent patterns to model user behavior. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve machine learning, social science, and database techniques that could be used in the proposed model.
